defs.docs:
Wasmer-runtime is a library that makes embedding WebAssembly
 in your application easy, efficient, and safe.

attributes.value:
deny(dead_code, missing_docs, nonstandard_style, unused_imports, unused_mut,
       unused_variables, unused_unsafe, unreachable_patterns)

defs.name: memory
defs.docs:
The memory module contains the implementation data structures and helper functions used to
 manipulate and access wasm memory.

defs.name: wasm
defs.docs: Various types exposed by the Wasmer Runtime.

defs.name: error
defs.docs:
The error module contains the data structures and helper functions used to implement errors that
 are produced and returned from the wasmer runtime.

defs.name: units
defs.docs: Various unit types.

defs.name: types
defs.docs: Various types.

defs.name: cache
defs.docs:
The cache module provides the common data structures used by compiler backends to allow
 serializing compiled wasm code to a binary format.  The binary format can be persisted,
 and loaded to allow skipping compilation and fast startup.

defs.name: Cache
defs.docs: A generic cache for storing and loading compiled wasm modules.

defs.name: LoadError
defs.docs: Error type to return when load error occurs

defs.name: StoreError
defs.docs: Error type to return when store error occurs

defs.name: load
defs.docs: loads a module using the default `Backend`

defs.name: load_with_backend
defs.value: fn (&self, key: WasmHash, backend: Backend) -> Result<Module, Self::LoadError>
defs.docs: loads a cached module using a specific `Backend`

defs.name: store
defs.value: fn (&mut self, key: WasmHash, module: Module) -> Result<(), Self::StoreError>
defs.docs: Store a module into the cache with the given key

defs.name: FileSystemCache
defs.docs: Representation of a directory that contains compiled wasm artifacts.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Construct a new `FileSystemCache` around the specified directory.
 The contents of the cache are stored in sub-versioned directories.

defs.name: Cranelift
defs.docs: Cranelift backend

defs.name: Auto
defs.docs: Auto backend

defs.name: Backend
defs.docs: Enum used to select which compiler should be used to generate code.

defs.name: variants
defs.docs: Get a list of the currently enabled (via feature flag) backends.

defs.name: to_string
defs.docs:
Stable string representation of the backend.
 It can be used as part of a cache key, for example.

defs.name: compile
defs.docs:
Compile WebAssembly binary code into a [`Module`].
 This function is useful if it is necessary to
 compile a module before it can be instantiated
 (otherwise, the [`instantiate`] function should be used).

defs.name: compile_with_config
defs.docs:
The same as `compile` but takes a `CompilerConfig` for the purpose of
 changing the compiler's behavior

defs.name: compile_with_config_with
defs.value: fn (wasm: &[u8], compiler_config: CompilerConfig, compiler: &dyn Compiler) -> error::CompileResult<Module>
defs.docs:
The same as `compile_with_config` but takes a `Compiler` for the purpose of
 changing the backend.

defs.name: instantiate
defs.docs:
Compile and instantiate WebAssembly code without
 creating a [`Module`].

defs.name: default_compiler
defs.docs: Get a single instance of the default compiler to use.

defs.name: compiler_for_backend
defs.docs:
Get the `Compiler` as a trait object for the given `Backend`.
 Returns `Option` because support for the requested `Compiler` may
 not be enabled by feature flags.

defs.name: VERSION
defs.docs: The current version of this crate.
